CLAUDE CODE COMMANDS

Core Session & Setup Commands
These commands are used when launching Claude Code or managing the environment. 
claude: Starts a new interactive coding session in the current directory.
claude --continue (or -c): Resumes the most recent conversation in the current directory.
claude --resume <id|name> (or -r): Resumes a specific session by its ID or display name.
claude update: Updates Claude Code to the latest available version.
claude auth login: Authenticates your session with your Anthropic Console account. 
Essential Slash Commands
Slash commands are built-in operations used within an active interactive session. Use the /help command inside the CLI to see a full authoritative list. 

