/init: Initializes a CLAUDE.md file to store project context, coding standards, and build commands.
/clear: Wipes the current conversation history to free up context window space.
/compact: Summarizes the existing conversation to reduce token usage while keeping key details.
/diff: Opens an interactive viewer to review uncommitted changes made by Claude.
/rewind: Rolls back the conversation or code state to a specific earlier checkpoint.
/config: Opens an interactive configuration panel to adjust themes and default behavior.
/cost: Displays the current session's token consumption and estimated dollar cost.
/btw: Allows you to provide additional context or side notes without adding them to the main conversation thread. 

